<i>noun</i>: 훈육 [후ː뉵], 훈련 [훌ː련], 훈계 [훈ː계/훈ː게], 종목 [종ː목], 절도 [절또], 도야 [도야], 교련 [교ː련] <i>verb</i>: 훈육하다 [후ː뉴카다], 훈련하다 [훌ː련하다], 훈련시키다 [훌ː련시키다], 훈계하다 [훈ː계하다/훈ː게하다], 제재하다 [제ː재하다], 가르치다 [가르치다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>훈육 [후ː뉵]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline; education; upbringing</dd><br>
<dd>성품이나 도덕 등을 가르쳐 기름.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching and raising someone to cultivate his/her personality or morality, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>훈련 [훌ː련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. training; drill; discipline</dd><br>
<dd>기본자세나 동작 등을 되풀이하여 익힘.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of learning basic postures or movements through repetition.</dd><br>
<dd>2. training</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 익히게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching another to help him/her learn a skill, task, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>훈계 [훈ː계/훈ː게]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline; caution; lesson; admonishment</dd><br>
<dd>타일러서 앞으로 잘못이 없도록 주의를 줌. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of admonish someone not to repeat his/her wrongdoing in the future; or such a persuasive utterance.</dd><br>
<dt>종목 [종ː목]</dt><br>
<dd>1. item; discipline; event</dd><br>
<dd>여러 가지 종류에 따라 나눈 항목.</dd><br>
<dd>Any of the categories into which something is classified.</dd><br>
<dd>2. share; stock</dd><br>
<dd>주식을 사고파는 시장에서 주식이나 증권을 내용과 형식에 따라 나눈 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Any of the categories into which stocks and bonds are classified by content and form in the market where stocks are traded.</dd><br>
<dt>절도 [절또]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동이 질서가 있고 정도에 알맞은 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Speech or behavior exhibiting discipline and integrity.</dd><br>
<dt>도야 [도야]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline</dd><br>
<dd>훌륭한 사람이 되기 위하여 스스로 몸과 마음을 훈련함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of training oneself physically and mentally in order to become a great person.</dd><br>
<dt>교련 [교ː련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. discipline</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 몸과 마음을 굳세게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of teaching someone to strengthen his/her body and mind.</dd><br>
<dd>2. school drill</dd><br>
<dd>학교에서 가르치는 군사 훈련.</dd><br>
<dd>Military training offered at school.</dd><br>
<dd>3. exercise; training</dd><br>
<dd>군인에게 군사 지식이나 기술을 가르치는 훈련.</dd><br>
<dd>A drill that teaches soldiers about military knowledge or skills.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt>훈육하다 [후ː뉴카다]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline; educate</dd><br>
<dd>성품이나 도덕 등을 가르쳐 기르다.</dd><br>
<dd>To instill and cultivate character or morality, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>훈련하다 [훌ː련하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. train; drill; discipline</dd><br>
<dd>기본자세나 동작 등을 되풀이하여 익히다.</dd><br>
<dd>To learn basic postures or movements through repetition.</dd><br>
<dd>2. train; educate</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 익히게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To teach another to help him/her learn a skill, task, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>훈련시키다 [훌ː련시키다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. train; discipline</dd><br>
<dd>기본자세나 동작 등을 되풀이하여 익히게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To learn basic postures or movements through repetition.</dd><br>
<dd>2. train; teach</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 익히게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To teach another to help him/her learn a skill, task, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>훈계하다 [훈ː계하다/훈ː게하다]</dt><br>
<dd>discipline; admonish; caution; teach a lesson</dd><br>
<dd>타일러서 앞으로 잘못이 없도록 주의를 주다.</dd><br>
<dd>To admonish someone not to repeat his/her wrongdoing in the future.</dd><br>
<dt>제재하다 [제ː재하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. discipline; block; prohibit</dd><br>
<dd>일정한 규칙이나 관습을 어기지 못하게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To prevent someone from breaking a rule or custom.</dd><br>
<dd>2. crack down on; sanction</dd><br>
<dd>법이나 규정을 어겼을 때 국가가 처벌이나 금지 등을 행하다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a government to impose a penalty or ban for violating a law or regulation.</dd><br>
<dt>가르치다 [가르치다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. teach; instruct</dd><br>
<dd>지식이나 기술 등을 설명해서 익히게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To explain knowledge or skills to help someone understand it.</dd><br>
<dd>2. teach; discipline</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 생각이나 습관 등을 바르게 고치다.</dd><br>
<dd>To correct wrong thoughts, habits, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. educate; school; train</dd><br>
<dd>돈을 내 주어 학교나 학원에서 공부하게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To put someone through a school or an institute by paying for his/her education.</dd><br>
<dd>4. show; tell; inform; explain</dd><br>
<dd>상대방이 모르는 사실을 알려 주다.</dd><br>
<dd>To let someone know about something he/she is not aware of.</dd><br>
<dd>5. teach</dd><br>
<dd>살아가는 데 필요한 태도나 가치를 알게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To make someone learn about a certain attitude or value necessary for a living.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>